Pantheon Rosetta Engine
The Rosetta Engine is the first executable translator layer for Pantheon Prime.
It treats the repository as natural-language source code, then compiles recurring
symbols into operational contracts.

It does not delete redundancy. It classifies redundancy as:

alias
journey route
flank route
evidence trail
failure mode
candidate concept
Run
python3 rosetta_engine.py --root . --output rosetta_report.md --json rosetta_report.json
Translate one phrase:

python3 rosetta_engine.py --text "Spider maps the invariant; Mirror checks it; Mother Duck logs it."
Translate one file:

python3 rosetta_engine.py --file "frontdoor/glossary light"
What It Emits
canonical concepts detected in the corpus
aliases seen for each concept
operational contract for each symbolic handle
source evidence snippets
strong co-occurrence routes
journey/flank routes
candidate terms to canonize later
Core Idea
Pantheon symbols are compression handles.

Spider is not only a word. It compiles to relation mapping.
Hound compiles to anomaly detection.
Mirror compiles to coherence checking.
Kintsugi compiles to break, repair, and strengthen.
Mother Duck compiles to provenance and ledger continuity.

The engine preserves both layers:

mythic handle -> operational function -> evidence -> runnable contract
That is the bridge from recursive book to executable system.
